{
  "text": "Fernandez de la Vega and Lueker [CITATION_1] showed that the classic bin packing problem admits an APTAS. This seminal work introduced rounding methods which are suitable for bin packing problems.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "10519631"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "10519631": {
      "title": "Bin packing can be solved within 1 + \u03b5 in linear time",
      "abstract": "For any listL ofn numbers in (0, 1) letL* denote the minimum number of unit capacity bins needed to pack the elements ofL. We prove that, for every positive e, there exists anO(n)-time algorithmS such that, ifS(L) denotes the number of bins used byS forL, thenS(L)/L*\u22661+e for anyL providedL* is sufficiently large."
    }
  }
}